==Old English==
===Etymology===
Common in Germanic and Romance languages, probably from Vulgar Latin ''*rattus'' (though some sources say the Germanic was borrowed into the Romance languages).  Compare Old Saxon [[ratta]] (Dutch [[rat#Dutch|rat]]), Old High German [[ratta]] (German [[Ratte]]), French [[rat#French|rat]], Spanish [[rata]], Italian [[ratto]].

